rap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eveningshadow>EveningShadow</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/16/03 11:29:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=142.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: War the greatest of all evils</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>The young Tier'dal unstraps and removes his heavy adamantite helm to get a better look at the elf.  He calls out from across the bar where he was sitting.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
..and where will your gods be when we kill your children?  Your family?  Your lovers?<br>
<br>
Will you be peaceful then?  Will your ideals be a balm that protects your dainty ears from their screams?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>He crosses the room, armor rattling as he weaves his way through the crowd to sit down across from the pale-elf</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <br>
<br>
Your ideals are a dream that will never be realized.  While you plead for peace we will continue to revel in the blood of everything you hold dear.<br>
<br>
I PRAY that you sit on your laurels, waiting for your &quot;sword of Marr&quot; to be unsheathed and come to your aid.  Your inaction will only breed a taste for vengeance... and vengeance begets hate.  Bring your crusade... ever drawn sword serves our Lords.<br>
<br>
You see, there is no course of action you may safely take.  Fight us and we rejoice in the pain, hatred and slaughter.  Even as we fall we fall knowing we have done our tasks and served our Lords well.  Do nothing and we bring that same pain... that same slaughter... on those you hold most dear.<br>
<br>
I wish you -all- the best in your proselytizing.  I hope you win many weak and war weary souls to your cause.  Lord Innoruuk and Mistress Saryrn  will gladly reap the rewards.<br>
<br>
~Vabris<br>
Cleric of Innoruuk, Acolyte of Saryrn<br>
<br>
