<br>
In many ways, you are correct.  Most do not make a conscious choice to follow an emotion... be it love or hate.. or the conscious choice to have a feeling... pain or pleasure... or an abstract concept such as honor or loyalty.<br>
<br>
However... there are those of us that do.  I would think from your words that you are not a devout gnome?  Many would argue that before the Gods there was nothing...  others would say that our own force of will created them to represent things we can not comprehend.  No matter to which school of thought you belong, none can deny that they exist now.  Some small few serve their ideals devoutly.  Not only do they pay lip service to their cause... such as a wounded man praying to Rodcet for salvation... but they actively pursue their portfolio.<br>
<br>
You are correct that all beings have the capacity to show faces of nearly every god... but there are those that seek to propagate our Gods' particular interest.<br>
<br>
You are wise to note that all Gods touch all beings in some ways...  The devout, however, seek to purge themselves of all but their Lords' most consecrated desires...  becoming an instrument of their will.  The hand of their God on Norrath, if you so choose to see it that way.  I do not wish to -feel- hatred and pain, I wish to -be- hatred and pain.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Vabris raises his hand, to stop any protest and continues</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
That being said, I am young.  I do not claim to be anything more then a devout follower.  Someday, through service, I will be blessed.<br>
<br>
That is no matter now though.<br>
<br>
For all the praise I have given your words, I will correct you in one thing.<br>
<br>
You have a pathetic understanding of what it is to be a Tier'dal.  We do not bemoan our circumstances.. we revel in them.  We do not hate because of what has been done to us in the past... We do not war to right some old atrocity.  You speak as if Lord Innoruuk's blessing on us was a curse...  Believe me, it is not.  We bear his scars and marks with a pride you could not even -begin- to understand.  Hate is not something that can be birthed... even the most malicious of my kind is so because of choices they make.  To claim anything less is a blasphemy.  We are not animals.  We do not lash out, we choose our own path.<br>
<br>
Your patronizing satire of the other races shows an ignorance on your part...  Perhaps you should seek a deeper understanding?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Vabris watches the gnomes reaction carefully, his back still to the pale elf.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
 <p>~Vabris<br>
Cleric of Innoruuk, Acolyte of Saryrn<br>
