<br>
Defeated?  I am no where near defeated, nor dejected.  You simply do not understand... and this illustrates it perfectly.<br>
<br>
You see my acceptance of my role as a Servent of Innoruuk as defeat...  There is no defeat or sucess in this matter.  Just as you do not choose to wake up an elf, I do not choose to wake up His insturment.  I merely am.  I am proud of that, and of my Service.<br>
<br>
All is not decided for us, even though we consider ourselves outside of Fate.  We make our own path in addition to the road the our Lord beakons us down.<br>
<br>
For example, I choose to follow Mistress Saryrn, for the power she grants me as one of her followers.  Not many are willing to accept her ways, but that matters little to me.<br>
<br>
I am neither dejected, nor defeated.<br>
 <p>~Vabris<br>
Cleric of Innoruuk, Acolyte of Saryrn<br>
