 &quot;Oy oy oy, me friend&quot;<br>
<br>
 *said the gnome, staring at the blue skinned elf*<br>
<br>
 &quot;Of course ye are no koada'dal with a dyed skin, elf, would be as sayin a barbarian is a gnome that got stretched upwards&quot;<br>
<br>
 *the small creature shrugged before crossing his arms*<br>
<br>
 &quot;But ye, as all species, share common basis, a common part of yer psyche that is all of us' lot. This ye cannot object, and it was what a meant.<br>
  As fer bein' given yer destiny... of course! tis ma point!<br>
<br>
 Yer words proved once again that ye can only consider this world through the optic of Hatred and it's teachings, wich were at first imposed ta ya, then ya decided ta follow, but why?<br>
 Haven't ye ever thought that mayhaps without havin' been taught directly the teachings o Innoruuk, ye might have seen the world with another eye? What tells ye ye wouldn't have chosen the way of hatred after?<br>
<br>
 oy, all the tier'dals are dedicated ta Innoruuk, but is it Innoruuk that decided so?...<br>
 ... or is it all b'cause of tha religious structure YE tier'dals built, and that leaves no chance fer comin back nor evolution?&quot;<br>
<br>
 *coughing politely, the gnome grabbed another cookie from the plate on his table*<br>
<br>
 &quot;What tells ye ye wud have been his instrument wud yer people have only worshipped the father of Hatred, and not entirely built their social structure through a distorted vision of all other principles, so that none choose but the path of hatred, or a very few that, my apologies, are but failures o' the tier'dal system escape only?&quot;<br>
